theorem dense_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x _
  -- First, compute that `interior (closure A)` is the whole space.
  have hInt : interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    have h₁ : interior (closure A) = interior (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      simpa using congrArg interior hDense
    simpa [interior_univ] using h₁
  -- Finish by rewriting with `hInt`.
  simpa [hInt] using (by
    simp : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X))

theorem dense_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense A) : Topology.P3 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  have h_closure : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hDense.closure_eq
  simpa [h_closure, interior_univ]
